## Pushing Updates to Droplet after Git Push
**Initial Only**

1. nano /root/update_site.sh
2. Enter into console:

        #!/bin/bash
        echo "--- Starting Update ---"
        cd /var/www/site1

        echo "1. Pulling latest code from GitHub..."
        git pull origin main # or 'master' depending on your branch name

        echo "2. Installing dependencies..."
        source /var/www/site1/DevelopWriter/bin/activate
        pip install -r requirements.txt

        echo "3. Migrating Database..."
        python manage.py migrate

        echo "4. Collecting Static Files..."
        python manage.py collectstatic --noinput

        echo "5. Restarting Gunicorn..."
        sudo systemctl restart site1

        echo "--- Update Complete! ---"

3. Make it executable, enter into console: 

        chmod +x /root/update_site.sh

After Git Push updates VS Code to GitHub, log into Droplet console and run deploy script:

        ./update_site.sh

Restart , Stop and Start the Nginx web server with:

    sudo systemctl restart nginx

    sudo systemctl stop nginx

    sudo systemctl start nginx

Get Nginx server status

    sudo systemctl status nginx


Install or Update all prerequisites using requirements.txt: 

> In Django, generate a requirements.txt file in the project directory with: pip freeze > requirements.txt

        pip install -r /var/www/site1/requirements.txt